The article is a statement made by the President of the United States, announcing the formal reestablishment of diplomatic relations with Cuba. The President describes this as a historic step towards normalizing relations with the Cuban government and people. He acknowledges the deep differences between the two countries in the past and the failure of the previous policy of isolation. The President emphasizes that the change is not just symbolic, but will lead to increased contact and cooperation between the US and Cuba, including in areas such as counterterrorism, disaster response, and development. He also mentions that while there will still be serious differences, the best way to support American values is through engagement and dialogue. The President calls on Congress to lift the embargo on Cuba, citing the support of the American people for this change. He concludes by expressing optimism for a better future between the two countries.